# 9) Update / redeploy workflow

### 9.1 Backend server update

```bash
cd ~/Gradion
git pull
docker compose -f docker-compose.yml -f docker-compose.backend.yml up -d --build
docker compose logs backend --tail 20
```

Migrations run automatically on backend startup. To seed test users (production image):

```bash
docker compose exec backend sh -lc "npm run prisma:seed:prod"
```

If the backend is restarting, use a one-off container:

```bash
docker compose run --rm --no-deps backend npm run prisma:seed:prod
```

### 9.2 Frontend server update

```bash
cd ~/Gradion
git pull
cd frontend
docker build -t gradion-frontend:prod -f Dockerfile .
docker rm -f gradion-frontend
docker run -d \
  --name gradion-frontend \
  --restart unless-stopped \
  -p 5050:3000 \
  gradion-frontend:prod
docker ps --filter name=gradion-frontend
curl -s -o /dev/null -w "%{http_code}\n" http://127.0.0.1:5050
```

If you see `502 Bad Gateway`, the frontend container is usually **not running** (check `docker ps -a`). A common mistake is an incomplete `docker run` line, e.g. `--restart` without `unless-stopped`.

Ensure `frontend/.env.local` exists **before** `docker build` (e.g. `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://api.gradion.id/api`).

### 9.3 Email (required for forgot-password & verification)

Password reset and verification emails fail with **400/503** when the backend cannot send mail.

1. On the **backend server**, edit `backend/.env` (not only `.env.example`):

```bash
# Option A — Resend (verify gradion.id domain in Resend dashboard first)
RESEND_API_KEY=re_xxxxxxxx
RESEND_FROM_EMAIL=noreply@gradion.id
RESEND_FROM_NAME=Gradion
FRONTEND_URL=https://gradion.id

# Option B — SMTP (e.g. Google Workspace)
# SMTP_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
# SMTP_PORT=587
# SMTP_SECURE=false
# SMTP_USER=noreply@gradion.id
# SMTP_PASSWORD=app-specific-password
# SMTP_FROM_EMAIL=noreply@gradion.id
```

2. Rebuild/restart backend:

```bash
docker compose -f docker-compose.yml -f docker-compose.backend.yml up -d --build backend
```

3. Verify configuration:

```bash
curl -s https://api.gradion.id/api/health | jq .email
# Expect: { "configured": true, "provider": "resend" } or "smtp"

curl -s -X POST https://api.gradion.id/api/health/test-email \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"to":"your-email@example.com"}'
```

**Note:** `docker-compose` loads `backend/.env.example` then `backend/.env`. Placeholder `RESEND_API_KEY` values in `.env.example` are ignored when SMTP is set. After editing `backend/.env`, **recreate** the backend container (a simple restart does not reload `env_file`):

```bash
docker compose -f docker-compose.yml -f docker-compose.backend.yml up -d --force-recreate backend
```

**SMTP configured but forgot-password still fails?** On the backend server:

```bash
# 1) Confirm SMTP vars are inside the running container (not only on disk)
docker compose exec backend sh -lc 'env | grep -E "^SMTP_" | sed "s/SMTP_PASSWORD=.*/SMTP_PASSWORD=***hidden***/"'

# 2) Tail logs, then trigger forgot-password from the browser
docker compose logs backend -f --tail 50

# 3) Test send (replace with your email)
curl -s -X POST http://127.0.0.1:5001/api/health/test-email \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"to":"you@example.com"}'

# 4) Confirm password_reset_tokens table exists
docker compose exec backend npx prisma migrate status
```

- Empty `SMTP_*` in step 1 → recreate backend after fixing `backend/.env` path.
- Logs show `Invalid login` / `535` → regenerate Google **App Password** (2FA required); use 16 chars **without spaces**.
- Logs show `password_reset_tokens` / Prisma P2021 → run `docker compose exec backend npx prisma migrate deploy`.
- Port 587 timeout → try `SMTP_PORT=465` and `SMTP_SECURE=true` in `backend/.env`, then recreate.

